HEADWORD: Autoptical
<hw>Au*top"tic*al</hw> <pr>(-t⟦icr⟧k*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>a'ytoptiko`s</grk>: cf. F. <ets>autoptique</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Seen with one's own eyes; belonging to, or connected with, personal
observation; <as>as, <ex>autoptic</ex> testimony or
experience</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

